cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with depth estimation from images using deep learning techniques.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as accurate depth estimation is important for robotics applications such as autonomous navigation.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a novel sub-pixel convolutional layer extension for depth super-resolution.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques for self-supervised monocular depth estimation.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also a possible category as the paper deals with synthesizing high-resolution disparities from low-resolution convolutional features, which is relevant to computer graphics.
